Question:
Given an array, print only even numbers.
Input:
int[] arr = {3, 2, 7, 8, 6};

Solution:-

Java 8 Streams print even numbers from int[] using Arrays.stream(arr).filter(n -> n % 2 == 0).forEach. For input {3, 2, 7, 8, 6}, prints 2, 8, 6.

#Step-by-Step Logic
Convert array to IntStream via Arrays.stream(arr). Filter evens: filter(n -> n % 2 == 0). Print with forEach(System.out::println).

#Java Implementation

import java.util.Arrays;

public class PrintEvenNumbers {
    public static void printEvens(int[] arr) {
        Arrays.stream(arr)
              .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)
              .forEach(System.out::println);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {3, 2, 7, 8, 6};
        printEvens(arr);
    }
}

Prints:
text
2
8
6

#Thought Process
Arrays.stream(arr) creates primitive IntStream (efficient, no boxing). filter predicate % 2 == 0 selects evens. forEach terminal prints. Preserves order.

#Edge Cases Analysis
Empty array: Nothing prints.
Null array: NPE on Arrays.stream(null).
No evens: Nothing prints.
Zero: Even (0 % 2 == 0).
Negatives: -2 % 2 == 0 even.
Single element: Prints if even.
